package Libraries.Accessibility

/*
    The PropertyObserver class provides functionality to output any property change 
    event from the system. An example of a property event would be a change in the
    graphic for the cursor.

    Attribute: Example

    AccessibilityManager manager
    PropertyObserver observer
    manager:Add(observer)

    manager:Start()
    manager:Stop()

*/

class PropertyObserver 

    /*
        This action is a blueprint function that receives an event from the system
        for the programmer to use.

        Attribute: Parameter event The event from the system.

        Attribute: Example

        PropertyObserver observer
        SystemEvent event
        observer:ReceiveEvent(event)
    */
    blueprint action ReceiveEvent(PropertyEvent event)

end